# Frenchify Project Rules

## Project Overview
Frenchify is a French Language Learning Management System (LMS) built with React (Vite), Firebase, and Express.js. The platform operates on a Freemium model with three user roles: Students, Teachers, and Administrators.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React 19.2.0 + TypeScript + Vite
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-based configuration)
- **Routing**: React Router DOM v7
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Backend**: Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage) + Express.js (Cloud Functions)

## Code Style & Conventions

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all `.tsx` and `.ts` files
- Define interfaces for component props with the `interface` keyword
- Use explicit types for function parameters and return values
- Prefer `React.FC` for functional components with typed props

### React Components
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Use `useState`, `useEffect`, `useNavigate`, `useLocation` as needed
- Component file names should be PascalCase (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `CourseCard.tsx`)
- Export components as named exports: `export const ComponentName: React.FC = () => { ... }`

### File Structure
```
src/
├── components/        # Reusable UI components (Button, Input, Badge, Layout, etc.)
├── pages/            # Student pages (Dashboard, CoursePlayer, Profile)
├── forms/            # Auth pages (LandingPage, Login, Register)
├── teacherPages/     # Teacher pages (TeacherDashboard, CourseEditor, MyQuestions)
│   ├── components/   # Teacher-specific components
│   └── TeacherLayout.tsx
└── App.tsx           # Main routing
```

### Routing Conventions
- **Public Routes**: `/`, `/login`, `/register`
- **Student Routes**: `/dashboard`, `/course/:courseId`, `/profile`
- **Teacher Routes**: `/teacher/dashboard`, `/teacher/questions`, `/teacher/course/:courseId/edit`, `/teacher/course/new`
- Use `<Layout>` wrapper for student routes
- Use `<TeacherLayout>` wrapper for teacher routes

## Tailwind CSS v4 Configuration

### Setup
- Configuration is in `src/index.css` using `@theme` directive (NOT `tailwind.config.js`)
- Import: `@import "tailwindcss";`
- Vite plugin: `@tailwindcss/vite` in `vite.config.ts`

### Design System Colors
```css
--color-azure-blue: oklch(from #0055a4 l c h);
--color-marianne-red: oklch(from #ef4135 l c h);
--color-emerald: oklch(from #10b981 l c h);
--color-gold: oklch(from #f59e0b l c h);
--color-slate-blue: oklch(from #6366f1 l c h);
```

### Typography
- Font family: `Inter` (imported from Google Fonts)
- Use `font-bold`, `font-semibold`, `font-medium` for emphasis
- Heading scales: `text-3xl`, `text-2xl`, `text-xl`, `text-lg`

### Component Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in JSX
- Avoid inline styles unless absolutely necessary
- Use `className` conditionally with template literals for dynamic styles
- Prefer composition over configuration for component variants

## Component Patterns

### Button Component
```tsx
<Button variant="primary" size="lg" isLoading={loading}>
  Click Me
</Button>
```
Variants: `primary`, `action`, `destructive`, `ghost`
Sizes: `sm`, `md`, `lg`

### Input Component
```tsx
<Input label="Email" type="email" name="email" required />
```

### Badge Component
```tsx
<Badge variant="free" />  {/* or "pro" */}
```

### Layout Components
- `Layout`: Student navigation (Blue accents, "Frenchify" branding)
- `TeacherLayout`: Teacher navigation (Indigo accents, "Frenchify Teacher" branding)

## Design Principles

### Visual Excellence
- Use modern, premium design aesthetics
- Implement subtle animations and hover effects
- Use curated color palettes (avoid generic colors)
- Implement glassmorphism and gradients where appropriate

### French Theme
- Subtle French flag color accents (Blue, White, Red)
- Use "Frenchify" branding consistently
- Teacher branding variant: "Frenchify Teacher"

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Grid layouts: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`

## State Management
- Use React `useState` for local component state
- Use `useNavigate()` for programmatic navigation
- Use `useLocation()` for route-based UI state (e.g., active nav links)

## Mock Data
- All data is currently mocked in components (MOCK_COURSES, MOCK_QUESTIONS, etc.)
- Use realistic data structures matching Firestore schema
- Include fields: `id`, `title`, `description`, `isPaid`, `tier`, `status`, etc.

## Role-Based Navigation
- Student login redirects to `/dashboard`
- Teacher login redirects to `/teacher/dashboard`
- Role selection toggle on Login page

## Freemium Logic
- Free tier: Limited access, "Upgrade to Pro" buttons
- Paid tier: Full access, no upgrade prompts
- Locked courses show lock icon for free users

## Best Practices
- **Performance**: Keep components focused and avoid unnecessary re-renders
- **Accessibility**: Use semantic HTML, proper labels, and ARIA attributes
- **Code Reusability**: Extract common patterns into reusable components
- **Naming**: Use descriptive names for variables, functions, and components
- **Comments**: Only add comments for complex logic, not obvious code
- **Imports**: Group imports (React, third-party, local components)
- **Error Handling**: Add proper error states and loading states

## Git Workflow
- Frontend code in `d:/MyProjects/Frenchify/frontend/`
- Backend functions in `d:/MyProjects/Frenchify/functions/`
- Use descriptive commit messages

## Testing & Verification
- Run `npm run dev` in frontend directory
- Test all routing paths manually
- Verify role-based redirects
- Check responsive behavior at different breakpoints

## Common Commands
```bash
# Development server
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview
```

## Notes
- PostCSS and legacy Tailwind config files have been removed (v4 migration)
- React import is optional in v19 but included for clarity
- All auth logic is currently simulated (no real Firebase integration yet)
